 728        private void TryClearGoalDatas_OwnershipChange(NetworkConnection prevOwner, bool asServer)
 0729        {
 0730            if (_clientAuthoritative)
 0731            {
 732                //If not server
 0733                if (!asServer)
 0734                {
 735                    //If owner now then clear as the owner controls the object now and shouldnt use past datas.
 0736                    if (base.IsOwner)
 0737                        _goalDataQueue.Clear();
 0738                }
 739                //as Server.
 740                else
 0741                {
 742                    //If new owner is valid then clear to allow new owner datas.
 0743                    if (base.Owner.IsValid)
 0744                        _goalDataQueue.Clear();
 0745                }
 0746            }
 747            /* Server authoritative never clears because the
 748             * clients do not control this object thus should always
 749             * follow the queue. */
 0750        }

 760        private void InitializeFields(bool asServer)
 0761        {
 0762            bool asClientAndNotHost = (!asServer && !base.IsServerStarted);
 763
 764            /* Even though these collections are nullified on clean up
 765             * they could still exist on the reinitialization for clientHost if
 766             * an object is despawned to a pool then very quickly respawned
 767             * before the clientHost side has not processed the despawn yet.
 768             * Because of this check count rather than null. */
 0769            if (asClientAndNotHost || asServer)
 0770            {
 771                //Prefer to reset existing.
 0772                if (_lastSentTransformData != null)
 0773                    _lastSentTransformData.ResetState();
 774                else
 0775                    _lastSentTransformData = ResettableObjectCaches<TransformData>.Retrieve();
 0776            }
 777
 0778            if (asServer)
 0779            {
 0780                if (_toClientChangedWriter != null)
 0781                    _toClientChangedWriter.Clear();
 782                else
 0783                    _toClientChangedWriter = WriterPool.Retrieve();
 0784            }
 0785        }

 787        /// <summary>
 788        /// Configures components automatically.
 789        /// </summary>
 790
 791        /// <summary>
 792        /// Configures components automatically.
 793        /// </summary>
 794        private void ConfigureComponents()
 0795        {
 796            //Disabled.
 0797            if (_componentConfiguration == ComponentConfigurationType.Disabled)
 0798                return;
 799
 800            //RB.
 0801            if (_componentConfiguration == ComponentConfigurationType.Rigidbody)
 0802            {
 0803                if (TryGetComponent(out Rigidbody c))
 0804                {
 805                    //If first time set starting interpolation.
 0806                    if (_initializedRigidbodyInterpolation == null)
 0807                        _initializedRigidbodyInterpolation = c.interpolation;
 808
 0809                    bool isKinematic = CanMakeKinematic();
 0810                    c.isKinematic = isKinematic;
 811
 0812                    if (isKinematic)
 0813                        c.interpolation = RigidbodyInterpolation.None;
 814                    else
 0815                        c.interpolation = _initializedRigidbodyInterpolation.Value;
 0816                }
 0817            }
 818            //RB2D
 0819            else if (_componentConfiguration == ComponentConfigurationType.Rigidbody2D)
 0820            {
 0821                if (TryGetComponent(out Rigidbody2D c))
 0822                {
 823                    //If first time set starting interpolation.
 0824                    if (_initializedRigidbodyInterpolation2d == null)
 0825                        _initializedRigidbodyInterpolation2d = c.interpolation;
 826
 0827                    bool isKinematic = CanMakeKinematic();
 0828                    c.isKinematic = isKinematic;
 0829                    c.simulated = !isKinematic;
 830
 0831                    if (isKinematic)
 0832                        c.interpolation = RigidbodyInterpolation2D.None;
 833                    else
 0834                        c.interpolation = _initializedRigidbodyInterpolation2d.Value;
 0835                }
 0836            }
 837            //CC
 0838            else if (_componentConfiguration == ComponentConfigurationType.CharacterController)
 0839            {
 0840                if (TryGetComponent(out CharacterController c))
 0841                {
 842                    //Client auth.
 0843                    if (_clientAuthoritative)
 0844                    {
 0845                        c.enabled = base.IsController;
 0846                    }
 847                    //Server auth.
 848                    else
 0849                    {
 850                        //Not CSP.
 0851                        if (_sendToOwner)
 0852                            c.enabled = base.IsServerInitialized;
 853                        //Most likely CSP.
 854                        else
 0855                            c.enabled = (base.IsServerInitialized || base.IsOwner);
 0856                    }
 0857                }
 0858            }
 859
 860            bool CanMakeKinematic()
 0861            {
 0862                bool isServerStarted = base.IsServerStarted;
 863
 864                //When not client auth, kinematic is always true if not server.
 0865                if (!_clientAuthoritative)
 0866                    return !isServerStarted;
 867
 868                /* If here then is client-auth. */
 869
 870                //Owner shouldn't be kinematic as they are controller.
 0871                if (base.IsOwner)
 0872                    return false;
 873
 874                //Is server, and there is no owner.
 0875                if (isServerStarted && !base.Owner.IsActive)
 0876                    return false;
 877
 0878                return true;
 0879            }
 0880        }

 882        /// <summary>
 883        /// Called when a tick occurs.
 884        /// </summary>
 885        private void TimeManager_OnPostTick()
 0886        {
 887            //If to force send via tick delay do so and reset force send tick.
 0888            if (_forceSendTick != Managing.Timing.TimeManager.UNSET_TICK && _timeManager.LocalTick > _forceSendTick)
 0889            {
 0890                _forceSendTick = Managing.Timing.TimeManager.UNSET_TICK;
 0891                ForceSend();
 0892            }
 893
 0894            UpdateParentBehaviour();
 895
 896            /* Intervals remaining is only used when the interval value
 897             * is set higher than 1. An interval of 1 indicates to send
 898             * every tick. Only check to wait more ticks if interval
 899             * is larger than 1. */
 0900            if (_interval > 1)
 0901            {
 902                /* If intervalsRemaining is unset then that means the transform
 903                 * did not change last tick. See if transform changed and if so then
 904                 * update remaining to _interval. */
 0905                if (_intervalsRemaining == -1)
 0906                {
 907                    //Transform didn't change, no reason to start remaining.
 0908                    if (!_cachedTransform.hasChanged)
 0909                        return;
 910
 0911                    _intervalsRemaining = _interval;
 0912                }
 913
 914                //If here then intervalsRemaining can be deducted.
 0915                _intervalsRemaining--;
 916                //Interval not met yet.
 0917                if (_intervalsRemaining > 0)
 0918                    return;
 919                //Intervals remainin is met. Reset to -1 to await new change.
 920                else
 0921                    _intervalsRemaining = -1;
 0922            }
 923
 0924            bool isServerInitialized = base.IsServerInitialized;
 0925            bool isClientInitialized = base.IsClientInitialized;
 926
 0927            if (isServerInitialized)
 0928            {
 929                /* If client is not initialized then
 930                 * call a move to targe ton post tick to ensure
 931                 * anything with instant rates gets moved. */
 0932                if (!isClientInitialized)
 0933                    MoveToTarget((float)_timeManager.TickDelta);
 934                //
 0935                SendToClients();
 0936            }
 937
 0938            if (isClientInitialized)
 0939                SendToServer(_lastSentTransformData);
 0940        }
 941
 942        /// <summary>
 943        /// Tries to subscribe to TimeManager ticks.
 944        /// </summary>
 945        private void ChangeTickSubscription(bool subscribe)
 0946        {
 0947            if (subscribe == _subscribedToTicks || base.NetworkManager == null)
 0948                return;
 949
 0950            _subscribedToTicks = subscribe;
 0951            if (subscribe)
 0952                base.NetworkManager.TimeManager.OnPostTick += TimeManager_OnPostTick;
 953            else
 0954                base.NetworkManager.TimeManager.OnPostTick -= TimeManager_OnPostTick;
 0955        }
 956
 957        private void ChangeUpdateSubscription(bool subscribe)
 0958        {

 1320        /// <summary>

 01324        {

 1440        /// <summary>

 01444        {

 01446                return;
 1447            //No permissions to set.
 01448            if (!CanControl())
 01449                return;
 01450            Transform parent = _cachedTransform.parent;
 1451
 1452            //No parent.
 01453            if (parent == null)
 01454            {
 1455                /* Check for being set without using nob.SetParent.

 1516        /// <summary>
 1517        /// Moves to a GoalData. Automatically determins if to use data from server or client.
 1518        /// </summary>
 1519        private void MoveToTarget(float delta)
 01520        {
 01521            if (_currentGoalData == null)
 01522                return;
 1523
 1524            //Cannot move if neither is active.
 01525            if (!base.IsServerInitialized && !base.IsClientInitialized)
 01526                return;
 1527
 1528            //If client auth and the owner don't move towards target.
 01529            if (_clientAuthoritative)
 01530            {
 01531                if (base.IsOwner || TakenOwnership)
 01532                    return;
 01533            }
 1534            else
 01535            {
 1536                //If not client authoritative, is owner, and don't sync to owner.
 01537                if (base.IsOwner && !_sendToOwner)
 01538                    return;
 01539            }
 1540
 1541            //True if not client controlled.
 01542            bool controlledByClient = (_clientAuthoritative && base.Owner.IsActive);
 1543            //If not controlled by client and is server then no reason to move.
 01544            if (!controlledByClient && base.IsServerInitialized)
 01545                return;
 1546
 1547            /* Once here it's safe to assume the object will be moving.
 1548             * Any checks which would stop it from moving be it client
 1549             * auth and owner, or server controlled and server, ect,
 1550             * would have already been run. */
 01551            TransformData td = _currentGoalData.Transforms;
 01552            RateData rd = _currentGoalData.Rates;
 1553
 1554            //Set parent.
 01555            if (_synchronizeParent)
 01556                SetParent(td.ParentBehaviour, rd);
 1557
 01558            float multiplier = 1f;
 01559            int queueCount = _goalDataQueue.Count;
 1560            //Increase move rate slightly if over queue count.
 01561            if (queueCount > (_interpolation + 1))
 01562                multiplier += 0.05f;
 1563
 1564            //Rate to update. Changes per property.
 1565            float rate;
 01566            Transform t = _cachedTransform;
 1567
 1568            //Snap any bits of the transform that should be.
 01569            SnapProperties(td);
 1570
 1571            //Position.
 01572            if (_synchronizePosition)
 01573            {
 01574                rate = rd.Position;
 01575                Vector3 posGoal = (td.ExtrapolationState == TransformData.ExtrapolateState.Active && !_lastReceiveReliab
 1576                // ReSharper disable once CompareOfFloatsByEqualityOperator
 01577                if (rate == -1f)
 01578                    t.localPosition = td.Position;
 1579                else
 01580                    t.localPosition = Vector3.MoveTowards(t.localPosition, posGoal, rate * delta * multiplier);
 01581            }
 1582
 1583            //Rotation.
 01584            if (_synchronizeRotation)
 01585            {
 01586                rate = rd.Rotation;
 1587                // ReSharper disable once CompareOfFloatsByEqualityOperator
 01588                if (rate == -1f)
 01589                    t.localRotation = td.Rotation;
 1590                else
 01591                    t.localRotation = Quaternion.RotateTowards(t.localRotation, td.Rotation, rate * delta);
 01592            }
 1593
 1594            //Scale.
 01595            if (_synchronizeScale)
 01596            {
 01597                rate = rd.Scale;
 1598                // ReSharper disable once CompareOfFloatsByEqualityOperator
 01599                if (rate == -1f)
 01600                    t.localScale = td.Scale;
 1601                else
 01602                    t.localScale = Vector3.MoveTowards(t.localScale, td.Scale, rate * delta);
 01603            }
 1604
 01605            float timeRemaining = rd.TimeRemaining - (delta * multiplier);
 01606            if (timeRemaining < -delta)
 01607                timeRemaining = -delta;
 01608            rd.TimeRemaining = timeRemaining;
 1609
 01610            if (rd.TimeRemaining <= 0f)
 01611            {
 01612                float leftOver = Mathf.Abs(rd.TimeRemaining);
 1613                //If more in buffer then run next buffer.
 01614                if (queueCount > 0)
 01615                {
 01616                    SetCurrentGoalData(_goalDataQueue.Dequeue());
 01617                    if (leftOver > 0f)
 01618                        MoveToTarget(leftOver);
 01619                }
 1620                //No more in buffer, see if can extrapolate.
 1621                else
 01622                {
 1623                    //PROSTART
 1624                    //Can extrapolate.
 01625                    if (td.ExtrapolationState == TransformData.ExtrapolateState.Available)
 01626                    {
 01627                        rd.TimeRemaining = (float)(_extrapolation * _timeManager.TickDelta);
 01628                        td.ExtrapolationState = TransformData.ExtrapolateState.Active;
 01629                        if (leftOver > 0f)
 01630                            MoveToTarget(leftOver);
 01631                    }
 1632                    //Ran out of extrapolate.
 01633                    else if (td.ExtrapolationState == TransformData.ExtrapolateState.Active)
 01634                    {
 01635                        rd.TimeRemaining = (float)(_extrapolation * _timeManager.TickDelta);
 01636                        td.ExtrapolationState = TransformData.ExtrapolateState.Disabled;
 01637                        if (leftOver > 0f)
 01638                            MoveToTarget(leftOver);
 01639                    }
 1640                    //Extrapolation has ended or was never enabled.
 1641                    else
 01642                    {
 1643                        //PROEND
 1644                        /* If everything matches up then end queue.
 1645                         * Otherwise let it play out until stuff
 1646                         * aligns. Generally the time remaining is enough
 1647                         * but every once in awhile something goes funky
 1648                         * and it's thrown off. */
 01649                        if (!HasChanged(td))
 01650                            _currentGoalData = null;
 01651                        OnInterpolationComplete?.Invoke();
 1652                        //PROSTART
 01653                    }
 1654                    //PROEND
 01655                }
 01656            }
 01657        }

 01663        {
 1664            //True if clientAuthoritative and there is an owner.

 01676                if (!_authoritativeClientData.HasData && _authoritativeClientData.Channel != Channel.Reliable && _author
 01677                {

 01683                        _authoritativeClientData.SendReliably();
 1684                    //Not enough time to send reliably, just don't need update.
 1685                    else
 01686                        return;

 01690                {

 1694                    //Now being sent data can unset.

 01704                ChangedDelta changed = GetChanged(lastSentData);

 1706                //If no change.

 1739        /// <summary>
 1740        /// Sends transform data to server if needed.
 1741        /// </summary>
 1742        private void SendToServer(TransformData lastSentTransformData)
 01743        {
 1744            /* ClientHost does not need to send to the server.
 1745             * Ideally this would still occur and the data be ignored
 1746             * for statistics tracking but to keep the code more simple
 1747             * we won't be doing that. Server out however still is tracked,
 1748             * which is generally considered more important data. */
 01749            if (base.IsServerInitialized)
 01750                return;
 1751
 1752            //Not client auth or not owner.
 01753            if (!_clientAuthoritative || !base.IsOwner)
 01754                return;
 1755
 1756            //Channel to send on.
 01757            Channel channel = Channel.Unreliable;
 1758            //Values changed since last check.
 01759            ChangedDelta changed = GetChanged(lastSentTransformData);
 1760
 1761            //If no change.
 01762            if (changed == ChangedDelta.Unset)
 01763            {
 1764                //No changes since last reliable; transform is up to date.
 01765                if (_clientChangedSinceReliable == ChangedDelta.Unset)
 01766                    return;
 1767
 1768                //Set changed to all changes over time and unset changes over time.
 01769                changed = _clientChangedSinceReliable;
 01770                _clientChangedSinceReliable = ChangedDelta.Unset;
 01771                channel = Channel.Reliable;
 01772            }
 1773            //There is change.
 1774            else
 01775            {
 01776                _clientChangedSinceReliable |= changed;
 01777            }
 1778
 1779            /* If here a send for transform values will occur. Update last values.
 1780             * Tick doesn't need to be set for whoever controls transform. */
 01781            Transform t = _cachedTransform;
 01782            lastSentTransformData.Update(0, t.localPosition, t.localRotation, t.localScale, t.localPosition, ParentBehav
 1783
 1784            //Send latest.
 01785            PooledWriter writer = WriterPool.Retrieve();
 01786            SerializeChanged(changed, writer);
 01787            ServerUpdateTransform(writer.GetArraySegment(), channel);
 1788
 01789            writer.Store();
 01790        }

 1858        /// <summary>
 1859        /// Gets transform values that have changed against specified proprties.
 1860        /// </summary>
 1861        private ChangedDelta GetChanged(Vector3 lastPosition, Quaternion lastRotation, Vector3 lastScale, NetworkBehavio
 01862        {
 01863            ChangedDelta changed = ChangedDelta.Unset;
 01864            Transform t = _cachedTransform;
 1865
 01866            Vector3 position = t.localPosition;
 01867            if (Mathf.Abs(position.x - lastPosition.x) >= 0.001f)
 01868                changed |= ChangedDelta.PositionX;
 01869            if (Mathf.Abs(position.y - lastPosition.y) >= 0.001f)
 01870                changed |= ChangedDelta.PositionY;
 01871            if (Mathf.Abs(position.z - lastPosition.z) >= 0.001f)
 01872                changed |= ChangedDelta.PositionZ;
 1873
 01874            Quaternion rotation = t.localRotation;
 01875            if (!rotation.Matches(lastRotation, true))
 01876                changed |= ChangedDelta.Rotation;
 1877
 1878            ChangedDelta startChanged;
 01879            startChanged = changed;
 1880
 01881            Vector3 scale = t.localScale;
 01882            if (Mathf.Abs(scale.x - lastScale.x) >= 0.001f)
 01883                changed |= ChangedDelta.ScaleX;
 01884            if (Mathf.Abs(scale.y - lastScale.y) >= 0.001f)
 01885                changed |= ChangedDelta.ScaleY;
 01886            if (Mathf.Abs(scale.z - lastScale.z) >= 0.001f)
 01887                changed |= ChangedDelta.ScaleZ;
 1888
 01889            if (changed != ChangedDelta.Unset && ParentBehaviour != null)
 01890                changed |= ChangedDelta.Nested;
 1891
 1892            //If added scale or childed then also add extended.
 01893            if (startChanged != changed)
 01894                changed |= ChangedDelta.Extended;
 1895
 01896            return changed;
 01897        }

 1955        /// <summary>

 01959        {
 1960            /* Only update rates if data has changed.
 1961             * When data comes in reliably for eventual consistency
 1962             * it's possible that it will be the same as the last
 1963             * unreliable packet. When this happens no change has occurred
 1964             * and the distance of change woudl also be 0; this prevents
 1965             * the NT from moving. Only need to compare data if channel is reliable. */

 01967            if (channel == Channel.Reliable && !hasChanged)
 01968            {
 01969                nextGd.Rates.Update(prevRd);
 01970                return;
 1971            }
 1972
 1973            float timePassed;
 01974            uint tickDifference = GetTickDifference(prevTd, nextGd, 1, out timePassed);

 01982            RateData rd = nextGd.Rates;

 01985            if (ChangedFullContains(changedFull, ChangedFull.Teleport))
 01986            {
 01987                SetInstantRates(rd, tickDifference, timePassed);
 01988                return;
 1989            }

 1991            //Correction to apply towards rates when a rate change is detected as abnormal.

 01996            if (ChangedFullContains(changedFull, ChangedFull.Position))
 01997            {

 02005                    if (distance >= _teleportThreshold)

 02019                {

 2021                    //Position distance already calculated.
 02022                    unalteredPositionRate = distance / timePassed;
 2023                    /* Try to detect abnormal rate changes.
 2024                     *
 2025                     * This won't occur if the user
 2026                     * is moving using the tick system but will likely happen when the transform
 2027                     * is being moved in update.
 2028                     *

 2030                     * which will result in distances being slightly different. This is
 2031                     * rarely an issue when the frame rate is high and the distance
 2032                     * variance is very little, but for games which are running at about
 2033                     * the same frame rate as the tick it's possible the object will
 2034                     * move twice the distance every few ticks. EG: if running 60 fps/50 tick.
 2035                     * Execution may look like this..
 2036                     * frame, tick, frame, tick, frame, frame, tick. The frame, frame would
 2037                     * result in double movement distance. */
 2038
 2039                    //If last position rate is known then compare against it.
 02040                    if (unalteredPositionRate > 0f && rd.LastUnalteredPositionRate > 0f)
 02041                    {
 02042                        float percentage = Mathf.Abs(1f - (unalteredPositionRate / rd.LastUnalteredPositionRate));
 2043                        /* If percentage change is more than 25% then speed is considered
 2044                         * to have changed drastically. */
 02045                        if (percentage > 0.25f)
 02046                        {
 02047                            float c = (rd.LastUnalteredPositionRate / unalteredPositionRate);

 2049                             * an abnormal detection. Fortunately abnornalties tend
 2050                             * to either skip a tick or send twice in one tick.
 2051                             * Because of this it's fairly safe to assume that if the calculated
 2052                             * correction is not ~0.5f or ~2f then it's a false detection. */

 02056                                abnormalCorrection = c;
 02057                            }

 2060                             * the values will fix themselves next tick, therefor when
 2061                             * rate changes drastically twice assume its intentional or
 2062                             * that the rate had simply fixed itself, both which would unset

 02064                        }
 02065                    }

 02068                    positionRate = (unalteredPositionRate * abnormalCorrection);
 02069                    if (positionRate <= 0f)
 02070                        positionRate = -1f;
 02071                }
 02072            }
 2073
 2074            //Rotation.
 02075            if (ChangedFullContains(changedFull, ChangedFull.Rotation))
 02076            {
 02077                Quaternion lastRotation = prevTd.Rotation;
 02078                distance = lastRotation.Angle(td.Rotation, true);
 02079                if (LowDistance(distance, true))
 02080                {
 02081                    rotationRate = -1f;
 02082                }
 2083                else
 02084                {
 02085                    rotationRate = (distance / timePassed) * abnormalCorrection;

 02087                        rotationRate = -1f;
 02088                }
 02089            }
 2090
 2091            //Scale.
 02092            if (ChangedFullContains(changedFull, ChangedFull.Scale))
 02093            {
 02094                Vector3 lastScale = prevTd.Scale;
 02095                distance = Vector3.Distance(lastScale, td.Scale);
 02096                if (LowDistance(distance, false))
 02097                {
 02098                    scaleRate = -1f;
 02099                }
 2100                else
 02101                {
 02102                    scaleRate = (distance / timePassed) * abnormalCorrection;
 02103                    if (scaleRate <= 0f)
 02104                        scaleRate = -1f;
 02105                }
 02106            }
 2107
 02108            rd.Update(positionRate, rotationRate, scaleRate, unalteredPositionRate, tickDifference, timePassed);
 2109
 2110            //Returns if whole contains part.
 2111            bool ChangedFullContains(ChangedFull whole, ChangedFull part)
 02112            {

 2116            /* Returns if the provided distance is extremely small.

 2129        /// <summary>
 2130        /// Gets the tick difference between two GoalDatas.
 2131        /// </summary>
 2132        private uint GetTickDifference(TransformData prevTd, GoalData nextGd, uint minimum, out float timePassed)
 02133        {
 02134            TransformData nextTd = nextGd.Transforms;
 2135
 02136            uint lastTick = prevTd.Tick;
 2137            /* Ticks passed between datas. If 0 then the last data
 2138             * was either not set or reliable, in which case the tick
 2139             * difference should be considered 1. */
 02140            if (lastTick == 0)
 02141                lastTick = (nextTd.Tick - _interval);
 2142
 02143            long tickDifference = (nextTd.Tick - lastTick);
 02144            if (tickDifference < minimum)
 02145                tickDifference = minimum;
 2146
 02147            timePassed = (float)base.NetworkManager.TimeManager.TicksToTime((uint)tickDifference);
 02148            return (uint)tickDifference;
 02149        }

 2235        /// <summary>
 2236        /// Processes received data for lcients and server.
 2237        /// </summary>
 2238        private void DataReceived(ArraySegment<byte> data, Channel channel, bool asServer)
 02239        {
 02240            if (base.IsDeinitializing)
 02241                return;
 2242
 02243            TransformData prevTd = (asServer) ? _lastReceivedClientTransformData : _lastReceivedServerTransformData;
 02244            RateData prevRd = _lastCalculatedRateData;
 2245
 02246            ChangedFull changedFull = ChangedFull.Unset;
 02247            GoalData nextGd = ResettableObjectCaches<GoalData>.Retrieve();
 02248            TransformData nextTd = nextGd.Transforms;
 02249            UpdateTransformData(data, prevTd, nextTd, ref changedFull);
 2250
 02251            OnDataReceived?.Invoke(prevTd, nextTd);
 02252            SetExtrapolation(prevTd, nextTd, channel);
 2253
 02254            bool hasChanged = HasChanged(prevTd, nextTd);

 2256            //If server only teleport.
 02257            if (asServer && !base.IsClientStarted)
 02258            {
 02259                uint tickDifference = GetTickDifference(prevTd, nextGd, 1, out float timePassed);
 02260                SetInstantRates(nextGd.Rates, tickDifference, timePassed);

 2269            /* If channel is reliable then this is a settled packet.
 2270             * Set tick to UNSET. When this occurs time calculations
 2271             * assume only 1 tick has passed. */
 02272            if (channel == Channel.Reliable)
 02273                nextTd.Tick = Managing.Timing.TimeManager.UNSET_TICK;
 2274
 02275            prevTd.Update(nextTd);
 02276            prevRd.Update(nextGd.Rates);
 2277
 02278            nextGd.ReceivedTick = _timeManager.LocalTick;
 2279
 02280            bool currentDataNull = (_currentGoalData == null);
 2281            /* If extrapolating then immediately break the extrapolation
 2282             * in favor of newest results. This will keep the buffer
 2283             * at 0 until the transform settles but the only other option is
 2284             * to stop the movement, which would defeat purpose of extrapolation,
 2285             * or slow down the transform while buffer rebuilds. Neither choice
 2286             * is great but later on I might try slowing down the transform slightly
 2287             * to give the buffer a chance to rebuild. */
 02288            if (!currentDataNull && _currentGoalData.Transforms.ExtrapolationState == TransformData.ExtrapolateState.Act
 02289            {
 02290                SetCurrentGoalData(nextGd);
 02291            }
 2292            /* If queue isn't started and its buffered enough
 2293             * to satisfy interpolation then set ready
 2294             * and set current data.
 2295             *
 2296             * Also if reliable then begin moving. */
 02297            else if (currentDataNull && _goalDataQueue.Count >= _interpolation || channel == Channel.Reliable)
 02298            {
 02299                if (_goalDataQueue.Count > 0)
 02300                {

 2303                     * enqueue latest. */
 02304                    if (hasChanged)
 02305                        _goalDataQueue.Enqueue(nextGd);
 02306                }
 2307                else
 02308                {
 02309                    SetCurrentGoalData(nextGd);
 02310                }
 02311            }
 2312            /* If here then there's not enough in buffer to begin
 2313             * so add onto the buffer. */
 2314            else
 02315            {
 02316                _goalDataQueue.Enqueue(nextGd);
 02317            }
 2318
 2319            /* If the queue is excessive beyond interpolation then
 2320             * dequeue extras to prevent from dropping behind too
 2321             * quickly. This shouldn't be an issue with normal movement
 2322             * as the NT speeds up if the buffer unexpectedly grows, but
 2323             * when connections are unstable results may come in chunks
 2324             * and for a better experience the older parts of the chunks
 2325             * will be dropped. */
 02326            if (_goalDataQueue.Count > (_interpolation + 3))
 02327            {
 02328                while (_goalDataQueue.Count > _interpolation)
 02329                {
 02330                    GoalData tmpGd = _goalDataQueue.Dequeue();
 02331                    ResettableObjectCaches<GoalData>.Store(tmpGd);
